{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_goyle_ver01/data/sn82007637/00516993820/1957083001/0898.xml":{"full_text":"I\nGOODMAN'S BAKERIES\nWK SPECIALIZED IN CAKES FOR ALL OCCASIONS\u201d\n2013 Canton Avenue\n16 E. Bancroft\n2858\nSylvania\nAvenue\nPOWERS\nQuality Shoes\nFor Children\nGReenwood 5-0351\nCHerry 1-9621\nCHerry 1-0595\n1844\nW. Bancroft\nNear Upton\nBEST W ISHES\nPrecise Tool Co.\n115 N. Westwood\nJO. 7143\nToledo Desk\nAnd Fixture\nCorporation\nMaumee, Ohio\nFor Health For Fun\nFor Eood Fellowship\nJOIN CENTRAL YMCA\n1110 Jefferson Ave.\nTry Massages and Steam Baths\nLearn Judo and W resiling\nFor Information Call CH. 3-7177\nPlay Basketball\nGreetings From\nWSPD-TV\nt\nCHANNEL\n13\nOn This Labor Day...\nmore than ever before, we look forward\nto an ever increasing area of under\nstanding between Management and La\nbor towards a goal of a strong and grow\ning Company with stability for all\nSURFACE COMBUSTION\nCORPORATION\nToledo, Ohio\nLabor Day Greetings\nfrom your 2 friendly\nBIG BEAR\nService Courtesy Economy\n3918 Monroe\n350 Central\n1\nNational Supply Unit News\nBy \u201cUNCLE REMUS\u2019*\nI\nHappenings around Shop.\nWe'll have to wait until next\nyear to receive a post card from\nany of the men I work with. No\nexcuse, fellows. you all had two\nand three weeks to write.\nThe Company spent in the\nneighborhood of $400 to install\nair lift on furnace door that\ndoesn\u2019t work. They try any\nthing to eliminate man power.\nThey would have been ahead\nby dividing money with help.\nIt was rumored about shop\nthat Roy Trimmer cut his vaca\ntion short because tool joint was\ngoing to work Saturday.\nThe Bowling League starts\nshortly, but where they will\nbowl nobody knows.\nGlad to see one of our better\nthe third\nforemen\nback\non\nshift.\nThe Company wouldn't hold\nstill on the picnic proposal. So\nit's back to turkeys and geese.\nRay Carters\u2019 Report.\nRay is back from A.S.A.\nMidwest Nudist Convention in\nLawrence, Kansas. He said,\n\u201cThere was 10 executive of\nficers, 150 delegates and a real\ncrowd of members and also\nmany visitors. All Conven\ntion Procedure was carried\non in the normal rules of the\norder. Religious Services was\nheld for all Faiths. All fam- l\nilies brought their children.\nThe Midwest Queen was a\nmember of Ray\u2019s club. The\nwas a 27-year-old\nQueen\nmother with 5 young daugh- i\nters. Hoping to see you all at\nthe 1958 Convention.\u201d\nPartially machined pieces that\nturn out to be scrap or salvage\nshould not be counted in with\nthe rest of the lot on the records.\nFor instance, one lot of alumi\nnum torgue converter castings\nhad to be salvaged 100% be\nfore the 1st operation could be\ncompleted. On the card it show\ned the whole operation 100%\ndone while not even 25\nof it\nThe\n,O\n'actually was machined.\nMethods Dept, noticed this boost\nin production. Naturally when\nthe next lot was machined the\noperators were behind the 8\nball. We all know that the\nMethod Dept. is lost without\nthese old records so why not\nhave them right.\nTwo new Committee\nmen\nwere elected Sunday, Aug. 25th,\nto replace J. Blesing and L.\nCarter. Election results: E.\nBrown 11, C. Calkins 13, H.\nMattimore 11, E. Fitzgarold 4,\nJ. Kondash 5, R. Riddle 6. Tie\nvote results between Brown and\nMattimore: Brown 11, Matti-!\nmore 18.\nSo there you have it C.\nCalkins and H. Mattimore,\nelected.\nDon\u2019t forget the Labor Day\nParade, this Monday, Sept. 2nd.\nDon\u2019t stand on the side lines.\nLet\u2019s make this a banner year.\nIt only takes two hours of your\ntime. Let\u2019s have at least 100\nmarchers.\n1\nGreetings From\nAyling\nReichert\nBy MARY WYATT\nA speedy recovery to the hus\nband of J. Anderson, who under\nwent surgery at Mercy Hospital.\nE.\nDabrowski doesn't care\nwhose car she goes home in,\njust so it's a black one.\nI\nWe are glad to hear that\nEsther is feeling better since her\nsurgery.\nA speedy recovery to the\nbrother of D. Schuster, who is\nrecuperating nicely, after a\nsevere heart attack.\nFor the last few weeks, the\nassembly room has looked like\na doily factory.\nI A speedy recovery to the\nbrother of M. Hughes, who is\nhospitalized.\nSomeone will have to inform\nD. Gwin that we don\u2019t quit for\nlunch at 10:00 a.m.\nA speedy recovery to Goldie\u2019s\nson-in-law,\nwho was injured\nwhile at work.\nAlso to Ann Joyce, who is\nhospitalized.\nIf you realize what it is to\nget a bat in your hair, ask A.\nNeipp, what it is to have one\nin your bedroom.\nWhen we see A Placko and F.\nSlippich in a long conversation,\nwe wonder what subject they\nare discussing.\nThanks to Atha for those deli\ncious peach cobblers. They sure\ndisappeared fast.\nA COMPLETE LINE OF\nQUALITY DAIRY PRODUCTS\nand Dependable Friendly Service\nat your Door or Favorite Store\nMilk Cream\nChocolate Milk\nGolden Guernsey\nSour Cream\nCottage Cheese\nButtermilk\nHalf and Half\nReddi Wip\ni\nI\nFresh Orange Juice\nI\nQuality V Chekd\n945 Berdan Avenue\nGReenwood 2-2114\nI\nLABOR DAY\nGREETINGS\nI\nTo All Members Of\nOrganized Labor\nI\nI\nDANA\nCORPORATION\nI\nToledo Division\nOrville A. Brown Pen Shoppe\nSheaffer Parker Eversharp Waterman Esterbrook\nPens And Pencils\nSPITZER ARCADE\nFYR FYTER SALES AGENCY\n419\u201412th Street\nCH 3-3635\nDETROIT BODY SHOP\n4601 Detroit Avenue\nGReenwood 4-8041\nA\nLabor Day Greetings\nACME SPECIALTY\nMANUFACTURING COMPANY\nToledo, Ohio\n\nJAMES G. CROCKETT\nInnuranre\n425 Gardner Bldg.\nCH 8-3505\nSHERIFF HIRSCH\nSAYS:\nuEnjoy Your Holiday and\nDrive With Extra Care\"\nSheriff Hirsch Staff\nTHE TOLEDO PORCELAIN\nENAMEL PRODUCTS CO.\nDivision of the Bettinger Corp,\nCOMPLETE ARCHITECTURAL\nPORCELAIN ENAMEL SERVICE\n2275 Smead Ave. CH. 4-9591 Toledo, Ohio\nA Labor Day Greeting to Our\nFriends and Customers In Organised Labor\nMhwANnJ\n.mpl\nBIG OR LITTLE\nYes, no matter how large or small the job is, you will\nfind us amply prepared to supply your needs. In our\none big store you can find all that is required by the\ncontractor for building a new house, or by the home\nowner adding a new shelf. If you are planning a new\ngarage, see us.\nMonthly Payments Available\nMaumee Lumber\nSupply Co.\nII\n711 Conant Street\nMaumee, O.\nLU. 3-3337\nth 41\nii\nI\nnil\nMLaa\nrp8\nA\nGreetings To All UAW-AFL-CIO\nMembers and Families\nAlso International Officers\nfrom\nDEFIANCE SCREW\nMACHINE PRODUCTS\n731 PERRY STREET\nDEFIANCE, OHIO\nI\nLABOR DAY GREETINGS\nSTONE\u2019S LUNCHEONETTES\n237\nSummit St.\n405 St. Clair St\nBeutler Red White Store\nFor Quality Foods At Lowest Prices\n705 South Street\nCHerry 6-0392\nSIEGLE DELICATESSEN\nCOMPLETE LINE OF KOSHER FOODS DELICACIES\n15 W. Bancroft\nCHerry 3-0254\nGreetings, AFL-CIO!\nDorr Street Hot Dog Chili Parlor\nOpen 24 Hours a Day\n1508 Dorr Street\nFINEST in FURNITURE\nHillebrand Brothers\n635 SO. ST. CLAIR ST.\nCH. 1-5842\nPARK HOTEL GRILL RESTAURANT\nTry Our Steaks, Chops and Fish Dinners\n207 Knapp St.\nCHerry 4-5553\nDo as smart athletes do drink lots of milk for good\nhealth and pep aplenty. It's rich in food values\nand flavor!\nBUY THE BEST-BUY\n62\nO\nSealtest\nCorrA\nCHEESE\nBUTTER\nSEALTEST QUALITY\nMILK ICE CREAM\nOhio Clover Leaf Dairy Co.\nAcademy of Medicine\nService Bureau\nIf Unable To Locate Your Doctor Call\nCHerry 1-2176\nLook for special \u201cIf no answer call\nCHerry 1-2176\u201d\nfollowing your doctor's regular listing\nFor reliable information about phyticiant\nand medical inttitutiont\nFor phyticiant in emergenciet where there\nit no family doctor\nAcademy of Medicine\noperated for the convenience of the public by\nACADEMY OF MEDICINE\n3101 COLUNG WOOD AVENUE\n24-Hour Service\nCLIFFORD\nC. LOSS, INC\nBUILDERS OF\nNATIONAL HOMES\nI\n\u201cCustom Built'\u201d\nFeaturing the 3-Bedroom\n\"SHOREHAM\"\n1,000 Square Feet of Space With\nLarge Kitchen Plus Dining Room\nI\nI\n\u201cTerms To Suit You*9\nNOTE: If You Are Eligible For GJ. Financing You\nCan Buy This Beautiful Home For $300.00 Down And\n$72.00 Per Month. ONLY 13 GJ. LOANS